#206\u001b[39m.\u001b[23;3HTwo harmless notes\u001b[Cfrom the output: \u001b[38;5;153mgit push -u\u001b[39m printed \"could not write config file\" because the sandbox's git config is\u001b[Cread-only,\u001b[Cbut\u001b[Cthe\u001b[Cpush\u001b[Cand\u001b[Cupstream\u001b[24;3Htracking both succeeded (I confirmed the ref\u001b[Con the remote). And \u001b[38;5;153mgh\u001b[39m warned about 11 uncommitted changes \u2014\u001b[Cthose ar\u001b[C the sandbox's own dotfiles (\u001b[38;5;153m.bashrc\u001b[39m,\u001b[K\u001b[25;3H\u001b[38;5;153m.gitconfig\u001b[39m, etc.), not part \u001b[Cf th\u001b[Cs work, so I left them alone.\u001b[K\u001b[27;1H\u001b[38;5;174m\u2722\u001b[CDiscombobul\u001b[38;5;216mati\u001b[38;5;174mng\u2026 \u001b[38;5;246m(1m 9s \u00b7 \u2193\u001b[39m \u001b[38;5;246m1.7k tokens)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[30;3H"]
